<section>
<title>Rounding Decimals</title>

<p>
This is a situation where our experience with whole numbers is valuable. Rounding a decimal number to a given place
value or a given number of decimal places is very similar to rounding whole numbers.
</p>

<example>
<title> Rounding to Tenths</title>
<p>

 <!-- Cite http://home.comcast.net/~cherylwilcox1/site/ Lesson 32  Example pg 4-->

</p>
<table class = "center">
  <tr>
<td align="right">Round <m>6.7291</m> to the nearest tenth.</td>
<td>Find the tenths place: one place after the decimal</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>6.\color{red}{7}291</m></td>
<td> <m>\color{red}{7}</m> is in the tenths place. The <span style="color:blue;">next</span> digit is the trigger.</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>6.\color{red}{7}\color{blue}{2}91</m></td>
<td>Since the trigger <m>\color{blue}{2}</m>  is less than <m>5</m>, we do not round up.</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>6.7</m></td>
<td>Our Solution</td>
  </tr>
</table>

</example>

<example>
<title> Rounding to Hundredths</title>
<p>

 <!-- Cite http://home.comcast.net/~cherylwilcox1/site/ Lesson 32  Example pg 4-->

</p>
<table class = "center">
  <tr>
<td align="right">Round <m>6.7291</m> to the nearest hundredth.</td>
<td>Find the hundredths place: two places after the decimal</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>6.7\color{red}{2}91</m></td>
<td> <m>\color{red}{2}</m> is in the hundredths place. The <span style="color:blue;">next</span> digit is the trigger.</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>6.7\color{red}{2}\color{blue}{9}1</m></td>
<td>Since the trigger <m>\color{blue}{9}</m>  is greater than <m>5</m>, we round up.</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>6.73</m></td>
<td>Our Solution</td>
  </tr>
</table>

</example>
</section>

<section>
<title>Estimation</title>

<p>
There are times when an estimate or approximation of an arithmetic operation is useful.  For example, when determining the reasonableness of a result.
</p>

<example>
<title> Estimating</title>
<p>

Estimate the product by rounding each of the given values to the nearest tenth.

</p>
<table class = "center">
  <tr>
<td align="right"> <m>5.924\times 6.675</m></td>
<td>Identify the triggers for each value</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>5.\color{red}{9}\color{blue}{2}4\times 6.\color{red}{6}\color{blue}{7}5</m></td>
<td> The trigger <m>\color{blue}{2}</m> is less than <m>5</m>: round down, the trigger <m>\color{blue}{7}</m> is greater than <m>5</m>: round up</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>5.9\times 6.7 </m></td>
<td>Multiply</td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td align="right"><m>39.53</m></td>
<td>Our Solution</td>
  </tr>
</table>



</example>
</section>
